`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `chunkDiffs$` observable is module-level singleton state — tests must call `clearAllChunkDiffs()` in `beforeEach` or they'll bleed state across test cases. The same pattern applies to the ECS `world`.
- Using `chunkDiffs$.peek()` (read without subscribing) is the correct pattern for imperative access in non-React code. Never call `.get()` outside a reactive context — it creates unintended subscriptions.
- `recordPlantedTree` follows the "accumulate into existing diff" pattern: it reads the current diff, appends the new tree, and writes back atomically. This avoids race conditions from concurrent modifications.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
